I WON'T BE ABLE TO PROPERLY

10:46.370 --> 10:48.429
MANIPULATE THE CRANIUM, SEE?

10:48.440 --> 10:49.907
Proctor: DR. TROY, WE ONLY HAVE

10:49.910 --> 10:50.979
A CERTAIN NUMBER OF BODIES

10:50.980 --> 10:51.969
DONATED TO SCIENCE.

10:51.980 --> 10:53.242
TO MATCH A CADAVER'S HEAD

10:53.250 --> 10:54.911
WITH EVERY SURGEON WAS NO SMALL

10:54.920 --> 10:55.716
FEAT.

10:55.720 --> 10:57.210
WE HAD TO PUT OUT A CALL TO

10:57.220 --> 10:58.312
4 COUNTIES TO MAKE SURE WE HAD

10:58.320 --> 10:59.389
ENOUGH.

10:59.390 --> 11:00.379
I'M SORRY, BUT YOU'RE JUST

11:00.390 --> 11:02.950
GONNA HAVE TO MAKE THIS WORK.

11:02.960 --> 11:04.825
[MERRIL LAUGHS]

11:04.830 --> 11:05.728
Proctor: LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

11:05.730 --> 11:06.924
THE FIRST OPERATION FOR BOARDS

11:06.930 --> 11:08.488
IS THE RHINOPLASTY.

11:08.500 --> 11:10.422
YOU HAVE ONE HOUR.

11:10.430 --> 11:11.328
AND...

11:13.270 --> 11:14.259
BEGIN.

11:14.270 --> 11:17.239
[TAPPING]

11:17.240 --> 11:18.730
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

11:18.740 --> 11:19.775
Sean: IF YOU'D RATHER NOT

11:19.780 --> 11:21.077
DISCUSS THIS NOW, WE DON'T HAVE

11:21.080 --> 11:23.139
TO, BUT I'M JUST SAYING I WENT

11:24.380 --> 11:26.143
ATLANTA WHO'S BEEN COMBINING

11:26.150 --> 11:27.378
INSULIN POTENTIATION THERAPY

11:27.380 --> 11:29.177
WITH THIS NEW DRUG UKRAINE.

11:29.180 --> 11:30.112
Megan: IS THAT DEBUSSY OR

11:30.120 --> 11:31.018
SCRIABIN?

11:31.020 --> 11:32.442
I ALWAYS GET THEM CONFUSED.

11:32.450 --> 11:34.884
Sean: UH, I WASN'T LISTENING.

11:34.890 --> 11:36.357
Megan: I KNOW.

11:44.230 --> 11:45.959
Megan: CLOSE YOUR EYES.

11:55.510 --> 11:57.102
Megan: I USED TO PLAY THAT WHEN

11:57.110 --> 11:58.338
I WAS A LITTLE GIRL.

12:03.090 --> 12:04.910
Sean: IT'S BEAUTIFUL, MEGAN.

12:04.920 --> 12:05.784
Megan: IT'S FUNNY.

12:05.790 --> 12:07.314
I HARDLY EVER PAY ATTENTION TO

12:07.320 --> 12:09.550
THE MUSIC IN A RESTAURANT.

12:09.560 --> 12:11.482
Sean: YOU HAVEN'T BEEN ON A LOT

12:11.490 --> 12:14.391
OF BAD DATES.

12:14.400 --> 12:15.219
I'VE HEARD SOME ENTIRE

12:15.230 --> 12:16.322
SYMPHONIES DURING SOME AWIQNARD

12:16.330 --> 12:17.467
SILENCES.

12:20.800 --> 12:21.960
Sean: MORE?

12:23.970 --> 12:28.031
Megan: NO, BUT FEEL FREE.

12:28.040 --> 12:29.849
Waiter: EXCUSE ME. ARE YOU DONE?

12:29.850 --> 12:31.909
Megan: YES. THANK YOU.

12:31.910 --> 12:33.013
Sean: YOU SURE? YOU BARELY ATE.

12:33.020 --> 12:34.112
Waiter: I COULD LEAVE IT HERE

12:34.120 --> 12:34.939
IF YOU LIKE.

12:34.950 --> 12:36.247
Megan: NO, REALLY, IT'S FINE.

12:36.250 --> 12:38.218
Sean: YOU WANT TO TAKE IT HOME?

12:38.220 --> 12:39.778
YOU MAY GET HUNGRY LATER.

12:44.890 --> 12:46.187
Megan: SHIT.

12:46.190 --> 12:46.929
Sean: UH...

12:49.260 --> 12:50.295
SORRY.

12:50.300 --> 12:51.221
Waiter: PLEASE, DON'T WORRY

12:51.230 --> 12:52.060
ABOUT IT.

12:52.070 --> 12:53.037
WE'LL GET THIS TAKEN CARE OF.

12:59.510 --> 13:00.499
Sean: I SHOULDN'T HAVE MADE YOU

13:00.510 --> 13:01.499
COME.

13:01.510 --> 13:03.546
YOU SAID YOU WERE TIRED.

13:03.550 --> 13:06.110
Megan: ARE YOU KIDDING?

13:06.110 --> 13:06.974
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO GET

13:06.980 --> 13:08.242
A RESERVATION AT THIS PLACE FOR

13:08.250 --> 13:10.115
YEARS.

13:10.120 --> 13:12.315
THAT'LL TEACH 'EM, DAMN SNOBS.

13:12.320 --> 13:15.187
[BOTH LAUGH]

13:15.190 --> 13:18.284
Megan: AT LEAST IT WAS ROMANTIC.

13:18.290 --> 13:19.325
Sean: THINGS'LL GET BETTER.

13:24.300 --> 13:25.289
[MEGAN SIGHS]

13:25.300 --> 13:27.495
Megan: YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK

13:27.500 --> 13:31.402
SO.

13:31.410 --> 13:32.263
AND NEITHER DO YOU.

13:34.880 --> 13:36.404
MY BODY IS EXPRESSING ITS

13:36.410 --> 13:39.004
OPINION VERY CLEARLY--

13:39.010 --> 13:42.912
UNCONTROLLABLE VOMITING,

13:42.920 --> 13:46.378
LOSS OF ALL MY SENSES,

13:46.390 --> 13:51.350
DIMINISHED LUCIDITY, A DRAMATIC

13:51.360 --> 13:54.557
INCREASE IN PAIN, AND A PRETTY

13:54.560 --> 13:56.255
EXCRUCIATING DEATH.

13:56.260 --> 13:57.158
Sean: AND I WILL BE THERE WITH

13:57.170 --> 13:59.320
YOU EVERY STEP OF THE WAY.

13:59.330 --> 14:00.297
Megan: THAT'S GOING TO MAKE IT

14:00.300 --> 14:01.494
PRETTY HARD TO KEEP THIS THING

14:01.500 --> 14:04.958
UNDER WRAPS.

14:04.970 --> 14:06.039
IF YOU'RE RUSHING TO MY SICKBED,

14:06.040 --> 14:07.974
JULIA'S LIKELY TO NOTICE

14:07.980 --> 14:12.679
AFTER A WHILE.

14:12.680 --> 14:14.170
I DON'T WANT A LONG-DRAWN-OUT

14:14.180 --> 14:16.444
DEATH, SEAN.

14:16.450 --> 14:18.247
I REALLY DON'T.

14:20.520 --> 14:24.650
I WANT A QUICK AND PEACEFUL ONE

14:24.660 --> 14:27.128
THAT'S UNDER MY CONTROL.

14:27.130 --> 14:28.097
Sean: THAT'S WHAT WE ALL HOPE

14:28.100 --> 14:29.328
FOR.

14:35.270 --> 14:36.498
Megan: I'M GOING TO DO MORE

14:36.500 --> 14:37.933
THAN HOPE.

14:54.060 --> 14:55.049
[MACHINE BEEPING]

14:55.060 --> 14:56.084
Christian: CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT

14:56.090 --> 14:57.421
BITCH INSINUATING I'M

14:57.430 --> 14:58.624
A TERRIBLE SURGEON WHILE SHE'S

14:58.630 --> 15:00.996
BLACKMAILING ME?

15:01.000 --> 15:02.092
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO LEFT THE

15:02.100 --> 15:03.692
CAUTERY TIP IN HER GUT, NOT ME.

15:03.700 --> 15:04.667
I'VE DONE SOME OF MY BEST WORK

15:04.670 --> 15:06.092
ON THE GRIM REAPER IN THERE.

15:06.100 --> 15:07.089
IF IT WEREN'T FOR ME, SHE'D

15:07.100 --> 15:08.237
LOOK HER AGE.

15:08.240 --> 15:10.105
WELL, SCREW HER.

15:10.110 --> 15:11.236
I MAY SLIP UP NOW AND THEN, BUT

15:11.240 --> 15:12.707
I AM NOT DEVOID OF SKILL.

15:12.710 --> 15:14.109
YOU MAY BE THE CARPENTER CHAMP,

15:14.110 --> 15:15.509
BUT I AM THE CONSTRUCTION

15:15.510 --> 15:16.374
WORKER AROUND HERE.

15:16.380 --> 15:17.472
I LAY THE FOUNDATIONS THAT YOU

15:17.480 --> 15:19.004
REFINE.

15:19.010 --> 15:19.601
Sean: THAT'S RIGHT.

15:19.610 --> 15:20.645
Christian: I'M GOING TO PASS

15:20.650 --> 15:21.969
THE RECERTIFICATION.

15:21.980 --> 15:23.208
I'M GOING TO WORK HARDER, BE

15:23.220 --> 15:24.016
LESS COMPLACENT.

15:24.020 --> 15:25.442
I'M GOING TO APPLY MYSELF AND

15:25.450 --> 15:27.657
NOT COAST BY ANYMORE ON SLICK.

15:27.660 --> 15:30.527
[WATER RUNNING]

15:30.530 --> 15:32.122
WE HAVE TO SWITCH HEADS.

15:32.130 --> 15:33.597
[SEAN TURNS OFF WATER]

15:33.600 --> 15:34.396
Sean: WHAT?

15:34.400 --> 15:35.628
Christian: I CANNOT PASS WITH

15:35.630 --> 15:37.063
THESE BIG MITTS AND THAT MIDGET

15:37.070 --> 15:38.264
HEAD, SEAN.

15:38.270 --> 15:39.066
Sean: YOU OPERATED ON

15:39.070 --> 15:40.162
A CADAVER HEAD IN COLLEGE.

15:40.170 --> 15:41.091
YOU PASSED.

15:41.100 --> 15:42.135
Christian: IN COLLEGE, THEY LET

15:42.140 --> 15:43.437
YOU SLIDE BY ON YOUTH AND

15:43.440 --> 15:44.737
HUBRIS.

15:44.740 --> 15:45.661
THEY'RE TOUGHER ON YOU IN

15:45.670 --> 15:47.035
THE RECERTIFICATION.

15:47.040 --> 15:47.574
LET'S FACE IT.

15:47.580 --> 15:48.672
I CAN DO A NOSE JOB AND

15:48.680 --> 15:50.204
CERTAINLY A BRILLIANT TIT JOB,

15:50.210 --> 15:51.677
BUT YOU'RE THE CRANIO-FACIAL

15:51.680 --> 15:53.716
MAN, SEAN, NOT ME.

15:53.720 --> 15:54.573
YOU DO ALMOST ALL OF OUR

15:54.580 --> 15:55.547
FACE-LIFTS.

15:55.550 --> 15:56.539
IT'S NOT MY SPECIALTY, AND

15:56.550 --> 15:57.414
WHENEVER I HAVE DONE THEM,

15:57.420 --> 15:58.341
YOU'VE BEEN THERE TO SUPERVISE.

16:00.790 --> 16:03.679
WHAT AM I GOING TO DO?

16:03.690 --> 16:05.328
I CAN'T FAIL, AND I CAN'T HAVE

16:05.330 --> 16:06.388
BOBOLIT LAUGHING AT ME,

16:06.390 --> 16:07.288
AND I CAN'T LET GRUBMAN BE

16:07.300 --> 16:08.119
RIGHT.

16:08.130 --> 16:09.199
Sean: PRACTICE MAKES PERFECT.

16:09.200 --> 16:10.360
Christian: OH, PRACTICE?

16:10.370 --> 16:11.291
PRACTICE ON WHAT, SEAN,

16:11.300 --> 16:12.460
MR. POTATO HEAD?

16:12.470 --> 16:13.698
IT'S NOT LIKE I CAN BRUSH UP ON

16:13.700 --> 16:16.589
A FETAL PIG.

16:16.600 --> 16:20.502
THERE IS ONLY ONE THING TO DO.

16:20.510 --> 16:21.374
KILL GRUBMAN AND PRACTICE ON

16:21.380 --> 16:24.178
HER.

16:24.180 --> 16:25.670
Sean: WHAT DID YOUR HEAD DIE OF?

16:28.080 --> 16:30.480
Christian: HEART ATTACK. YOURS?

16:30.490 --> 16:32.708
Sean: SUICIDE.

16:32.720 --> 16:35.587
YOU BELIEVE IN THAT?

16:35.590 --> 16:36.614
Christian: I THINK IF A PERSON

16:36.620 --> 16:38.258
IS IN A GREAT DEAL OF PAIN,

16:38.260 --> 16:39.284
PHYSICAL OR SPIRITUAL,

16:39.290 --> 16:40.291
AND TH EY'VE EXHAUSTED ALL THEIR

16:40.300 --> 16:41.722
OPTIONS, I WOULDN'T JUDGE THEM

16:41.730 --> 16:43.459
FOR IT.

16:43.470 --> 16:44.721
I'D SAY A SILENT PRAYER AND HOPE

16:44.730 --> 16:45.697
THEY FOUND THE PEACE LIFE

16:45.700 --> 16:47.361
COULDN'T GIVE THEM.

16:49.400 --> 16:50.537
I'LL ASSIST WITH THE BEEF

16:50.540 --> 16:51.609
CURTAINS, AND THEN WE'LL WHEEL

16:51.610 --> 16:52.668
IN COLONEL SANDERS.

17:05.090 --> 17:07.081
Liz: FORGIVE ME?

17:07.090 --> 17:08.250
Christian: WELL, YOU DID SAVE ME

17:08.260 --> 17:10.251
FROM A NEGLIGENCE SUIT.

17:10.260 --> 17:11.181
WHY NOT?

17:11.190 --> 17:12.179
Liz: THE VERY FACT THAT WE CAN

17:12.190 --> 17:13.498
CONTINUE TO COEXIST IN

17:13.500 --> 17:16.253
SEMI-HATRED--I AM BATHED IN

17:16.260 --> 17:17.295
RELIEF.

17:17.300 --> 17:20.235
[CHRISTIAN LAUGHS]

17:20.240 --> 17:23.664
Christian: ANYTHING INTERESTING?

17:23.670 --> 17:25.308
Liz: SLOW NEWS DAY.

17:25.310 --> 17:26.265
MORE SCANDAL IN THE POLICE

17:26.270 --> 17:27.134
DEPARTMENT.

17:27.140 --> 17:30.177
A LITTLE OLD HOMELESS LADY DIED.

17:30.180 --> 17:31.101
Christian: LITTLE?

17:31.110 --> 17:32.748
Liz: A JANE DOE FOUND UNCLAIMED

17:32.750 --> 17:34.570
AND DEAD UNDERNEATH A PALM AT

17:34.580 --> 17:35.672
THE BEACH.

17:35.680 --> 17:36.647
Christian: FOUL PLAY?

17:36.650 --> 17:38.242
Liz: NATURAL CAUSES.

17:38.250 --> 17:39.217
THEY THINK SHE WENT TO SIT DOWN

17:39.220 --> 17:40.357
TO REST AND KICKED.

17:40.360 --> 17:41.782
POOR THING, SHE HAD NO I.D.

17:41.790 --> 17:42.654
THEY SUSPECT SHE WAS AROUND

17:42.660 --> 17:44.389
80 YEARS OLD.

17:44.390 --> 17:46.551
Christian: WEIGHT?

17:46.560 --> 17:49.290
Liz: 5 FOOT TALL, 98 POUNDS.

17:49.300 --> 17:51.564
SAD.

17:51.570 --> 17:53.663
[WOMAN SINGING INDISTINCT LY]

18:10.450 --> 18:11.439
Guard: IF YOU WANT TO SEE DEAD

18:11.450 --> 18:13.452
PEOPLE, YOU CHECK WITH ME FIRST.

18:13.460 --> 18:14.654
Christian: CORONER'S OFFICE,

18:14.660 --> 18:15.809
CHRISTIAN TROY.

18:15.820 --> 18:16.684
I'M HERE TO INVESTIGATE

18:16.690 --> 18:18.726
A CERTAIN SOUTH BEACH JANE DOE.

18:18.730 --> 18:20.925
Guard: I.D.?

18:20.930 --> 18:22.420
Christian, laughs: I MUST'VE

18:22.430 --> 18:23.567
LEFT IT AT HOME.

18:23.570 --> 18:25.788
Guard: SHAME.

18:25.800 --> 18:26.767
Christian: LOOK, I'M HERE ON

18:26.770 --> 18:27.737
OFFICIAL BUSINESS.

18:27.740 --> 18:29.833
Guard: OH, IT'S OFFICIAL

18:29.840 --> 18:30.829
BUSINESS.

18:30.840 --> 18:32.808
THAT'S DIFFERENT.

18:32.810 --> 18:33.708
Christian: WHAT OTHER KIND OF

18:33.710 --> 18:34.529
BUSINESS WOULD I HAVE WITH

18:34.540 --> 18:35.575
A CORPSE?

18:35.580 --> 18:36.831
Guard: MONKEY BUSINESS.

18:36.840 --> 18:39.172
2 MONTHS AGO, I WALKED IN ON

18:39.180 --> 18:40.909
A GUY GETTING HIS FREAK ON WITH

18:40.920 --> 18:43.309
HIS DEAD EX.

18:43.320 --> 18:44.218
WANTED TO DO IT ONCE WITHOUT

18:44.220 --> 18:45.642
HER CRITICIZING.

18:49.220 --> 18:50.255
Christian: I DON'T USUALLY GET

18:50.260 --> 18:51.454
CRITICIZED.

18:51.460 --> 18:54.850
[THUD]

18:54.860 --> 18:56.828
Guard: I BET YOU DON'T--

18:56.830 --> 19:00.266
NOT LOOKING LIKE THAT--

19:00.270 --> 19:03.535
GUCCI SUIT, ROLEX--

19:03.540 --> 19:06.202
ONE FANCY CORONER.

19:06.210 --> 19:07.199
I'M GUESSING YOU'RE EITHER

19:07.210 --> 19:08.336
MOONLIGHTING AS AN INVESTMENT

19:08.340 --> 19:10.444
BANKER, OR YOU'RE STEALING THIS

19:10.450 --> 19:13.647
SHIT OFF OF DEAD PEOPLE.

19:13.650 --> 19:14.912
NOW YOU BETTER TELL ME WHAT YOU

19:14.920 --> 19:16.774
WANT AND WHY YOU'RE HERE, OR

19:16.780 --> 19:18.213
ELSE I'M GOING TO TELL SECURITY

19:18.220 --> 19:19.346
THAT WE HAVE A PROBLEM WITH

19:19.350 --> 19:22.558
A MALE MODEL NECROPHILIAC.

19:22.560 --> 19:25.358
Christian: I LIKE YOUR COLOGNE.

19:25.360 --> 19:26.622
LAGERFELD?

19:26.630 --> 19:28.257
Guard: DIALING.

19:28.260 --> 19:29.192
WH--

19:31.830 --> 19:33.764
Christian: ALL RIGHT.

19:33.770 --> 19:34.691
I'M A PLASTIC SURGEON.

19:34.700 --> 19:36.258
Guard: HONEY, IT'S WAY TOO LATE

19:36.270 --> 19:37.464
FOR THESE PEOPLE.

19:37.470 --> 19:38.402
Christian: I JUST NEED THE RIGHT

19:38.410 --> 19:39.365
KIND OF HEAD.

19:39.370 --> 19:41.509
Guard: OH.

19:41.510 --> 19:42.738
OK.

19:42.740 --> 19:44.640
Christian: TO PRACTICE ON.

19:44.650 --> 19:45.605
I'M TAKING AN EXAM, AND IF

19:45.610 --> 19:47.840
I FAIL, I'M SCREWED.

19:47.850 --> 19:51.684
Guard: SHIT.

19:51.690 --> 19:52.588
YOU WANT TO PRACTICE ON

19:52.590 --> 19:54.785
JANE DOE?

19:54.790 --> 19:56.815
WELL, I'M ALL ABOUT A TRADE.

19:56.820 --> 19:57.752
Christian: I COULD GIVE YOU SOME

19:57.760 --> 19:58.829
NEW PECS.

19:58.830 --> 19:59.854
Guard: THERE AIN'T NOTHING WRONG

19:59.860 --> 20:00.952
WITH MY PECS.

20:00.960 --> 20:02.791
WORKED MY ASS OFF FOR THESE

20:02.800 --> 20:03.698
PECS.

20:13.640 --> 20:16.029
I NEVER...

20:16.040 --> 20:16.779
LIKED MY CHIN.

20:23.490 --> 20:27.586
Guard: YOU'VE GOT ONE HOUR.

20:27.590 --> 20:28.955
I'LL COME BY NEXT WEEK TO

20:28.960 --> 20:30.211
SCHEDULE.

20:32.860 --> 20:34.452
[SCOFFS]

20:49.780 --> 20:51.372
IT SUCKS GETTING OLD, DOESN'T

20:51.380 --> 20:52.540
IT?

21:04.690 --> 21:06.578
Sean: NO PICTURES OF ME?

21:06.590 --> 21:07.591
Megan: I'LL HAVE MEMORIES OF

21:07.600 --> 21:10.467
YOU, AND YOU'LL HAVE MEMORIES

21:10.470 --> 21:13.337
OF ME.

21:13.340 --> 21:16.889
Sean: WE CAN MAKE MORE MEMORIES.

21:16.900 --> 21:19.004
WE COULD GO TO PARIS.

21:19.010 --> 21:20.068
Megan: I ALWAYS WANTED TO GO TO

21:20.070 --> 21:23.949
PARIS, BUT IF YOU CAN ONLY WALK

21:23.950 --> 21:25.679
FOR A FEW MINUTES

21:25.680 --> 21:26.601
AND YOU CAN'T DRINK ALL THAT

21:26.610 --> 21:31.013
WINE AND YOU CAN'T HAVE SEX,

21:31.020 --> 21:31.918
ALL YOU'VE GOT IS

21:31.920 --> 21:34.559
THE ARCHITECTURE.

21:34.560 --> 21:35.481
AND I'M NOT SO MUCH FOR

21:35.490 --> 21:36.809
ARCHITECTURE.

21:40.400 --> 21:41.719
Sean: BUT YOU LIKE THIS MOTEL

21:41.730 --> 21:43.095
BY THE SEA.

21:43.100 --> 21:48.629
Megan: NO. I LIKE THIS ROOM.

21:48.640 --> 21:50.904
THIS ROOM WAS THE LAST PLACE

21:50.910 --> 21:52.059
I FELT HAPPY.

21:54.910 --> 21:56.104
THIS ROOM IS THE LAST PLACE

21:56.110 --> 21:59.443
I FELT HOPE.

21:59.450 --> 22:02.112
[SIGHS]

22:02.120 --> 22:03.382
AND YOU HEARD WHAT THE DOCTOR

22:03.390 --> 22:04.049
SAID, SEAN.

22:04.050 --> 22:05.688
THERE IS NO MORE HOPE.

22:09.160 --> 22:14.826
ALL I CAN HOPE FOR IS DIGNITY

22:14.830 --> 22:17.924
AND A NICE SUNSET TOMORROW.

22:17.930 --> 22:19.158
Sean: I WON'T LET YOU DO THIS.

22:19.170 --> 22:20.432
Megan: IT'S NOT YOUR DECISION.

22:20.440 --> 22:21.464
Sean: I JUST FOUND YOU.

22:21.470 --> 22:22.459
Megan: AND NOW YOU HAVE TO LET

22:22.470 --> 22:23.732
ME GO.

22:25.970 --> 22:29.599
I DON'T FEAR DEATH, SEAN.

22:29.610 --> 22:33.546
I FEAR THE PROLONGMENT OF IT.

22:33.550 --> 22:36.474
Sean: I CAN'T CONDONE THIS OR

22:36.480 --> 22:37.549
HELP YOU, MEGAN.

22:37.550 --> 22:39.142
THIS IS RASH.

22:39.150 --> 22:40.686
Megan: THIS IS RIGHT.

22:46.830 --> 22:52.769
[SIGHS] IT'S LIKE...

22:52.770 --> 22:54.089
WHEN YOU'RE A KID AT

22:54.100 --> 22:56.762
AN AMUSEMENT PARK, AND YOU'RE

22:56.770 --> 22:58.965
HAVING THE GREATEST TIME.

22:58.970 --> 23:02.030
ICE CREAM AND FERRIS WHEELS AND

23:02.040 --> 23:05.100
STUFFED ANIMALS.

23:05.110 --> 23:07.510
AND IT GETS LATE, AND YOU BEG

23:07.520 --> 23:09.841
YOUR PARENTS TO LET YOU STAY.

23:09.850 --> 23:11.112
YOU'LL BE SO GOOD.

23:11.120 --> 23:14.487
YOU'LL DO ANYTHING THEY ASK.

23:14.490 --> 23:19.189
SO THEY SAY, "OK."

23:19.190 --> 23:21.750
ONLY NOW...

23:21.760 --> 23:24.126
THE STEPS ARE HARDER TO CLIMB.

23:24.130 --> 23:26.928
YOU HAVE A TUMMYACHE, AND YOU'RE

23:26.930 --> 23:28.238
TOO TIRED TO WAIT IN LINE

23:28.240 --> 23:32.700
FOR THE RIDES ANYMORE.

23:32.710 --> 23:38.899
AND SUDDENLY YOU BEGIN TO CRY.

23:38.910 --> 23:41.117
[SOBS]

23:56.160 --> 24:00.893
IT'S NO FUN ANYMORE.

24:00.900 --> 24:07.908
[SOBBING]

24:07.910 --> 24:10.902
AND YOU HEAR YOUR MOM'S VOICE

24:10.910 --> 24:12.639
SAYING, "MEGAN, WHEN ARE YOU

24:12.650 --> 24:15.847
GONNA LEARN ENOUGH'S ENOUGH?"

24:21.860 --> 24:24.954
[SIGHS]

